transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Good morning. Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: I was calling to cancel my standing order, and I got an email that said I had to call you to do that.

Speaker 1: Okay. We can help you with this. Can I have your name as well as your date of birth?

Speaker 2: Gregory Smith. You said date of birth?

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: 4-21-55.

Speaker 1: Thank you. And while I'm pulling up your account, Mr. Smith, may I ask the reason for wanting to cancel your prescription?

Speaker 2: Well, I just can't tolerate the Viagra. Too much dry mouth and dried up sinuses, sinus headache.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I just can't do that. I don't know how much is the Cialis.

Speaker 1: For Cialis, we do have it in the daily form as well as the on-demand. Do you know which one you'll be interested in?

Speaker 2: Probably the on-demand.

Speaker 1: For the on-demand, it starts at $10 a pill, but we do have a special right now. We have 12 pills for $89.

Speaker 2: Or you can do the deal of the month, which is 50 pills for $249.

Speaker 1: I can send you a free sample of the Cialis if you want to try it out.

Speaker 2: Probably not, because that's out of my ballpark for the budget price.

Speaker 1: I see. Okay. Well, if you do decide on wanting to take it down the line, you can always give us a call.

Speaker 2: Okay. I appreciate that.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you're welcome. Well, your prescription for the Viagra has been canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You as well. Bye.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye.
